            "answer_text": "Thanks for the A2A Archit Bhattacharya . Yes, the Naruto Novels are canon. These Novels have been co-written, supervised and approved by Kishimoto himself. Heck Kishi himself has taken the liberty to illustrate the cover pages of each of these novels.  Some haters often try to diss the Novels and moot them as non-canon material. They believe that novels contradict anime canon which in fact is absolutely false. ! It\u2019s the anime that contradicts the novels and not the other way around. They novels serve as source material for the anime . It is Studio Pierrot who fucks up the storyline of the novels and messes up the timeline and the order in which they have to be adapted into. For instance , let me give you some examples. I\u2019ll now compare the storyline of the novels and it\u2019s respective anime adaptaions. 1> Itachi Shinden Novels ( Vol 1 and 2)  Here\u2019s what happened in the anime adaption of it. Revolved around Itachi\u2019s life in the Ninja Academy.Showed his growth from a genin to an anbu elite.Animated the Itachi and Shisui vs rogue anbu fight.Shisui\u2019s death.Itachi murders his clan and joins the Akatsuki.Now here\u2019s what the anime failed to adapt from the Novel. Itachi and kid Naruto were actually on good terms with each other.Itachi and Shisui went on a hell lot of missions together.Itachi and Shisui fought a bootleg Hyuga and had a crushing defeat in his hands.Fugaku never had a Mangekyo Sharingan.Itachi was the one who killed his waifu (Izumi Uchiha) and not Obito. Itachi put her under a genjutsu where she spent an entire life growing up and marrying Itachi and eventually dying with him. Itachi gave her a painless death after doing so.Here\u2019s when the Itachi novels were published .  and here\u2019s when it was adapted into the anime.  So you tell me which source material is more reliable.  2> Shikamaru Hiden Novel Now Studio Pierrot fucked up big time. This Novel\u2019s timeline fits in before \u201cThe Last\u201d but they animated and adapted it after the movie\u2019s timeline.  The anime did adapt 99% of what happened in the novel but the order in which it was adapted fucked it up. Also here\u2019s when the novel was released:  and here\u2019s when it was animated :  So you tell me which source material is more reliable.  3>Sasuke Shinden : Book of Sunrise Novel  Again, wrong timeline. This novel actually takes place 5 months after Naruto and Hinata get married, however SP animated it before their marriage. The anime adapted 90% of what happened in the novel but never contradicted what happened in it, some I\u2019m cool with it. Here\u2019 the novel\u2019s release date :  and here\u2019s when it was adapted into the anime :  So you tell me which source material is more reliable.  4> Konoha Hiden: The Perfect Day for a Wedding Novel  This was a slice of life novel but it\u2019s canon nonetheless. The anime adapted almost everything that takes place in the novel. Here\u2019s when the novel was released :  And here\u2019s when it was adapted into the anime :  So you tell me which source material is more reliable.  5> Naruto Shinden : Parent and Child Day Novel  Now there are a lot of differences between the anime and the novel. Here\u2019s what the anime showed us : Naruto, Sasuke and Choji\u2019s POV.Boruto roams around the village aimlessly.And here\u2019s what happened in the novel: Boruto never left his home and slept through the entire day.It focuses mostly on Hinata who was on a mission with Hiashi, Hanabi and a bunch of other Hyugas and this clearly shows that Hinata continues to be an active ninja.Hinata fights Hanabi and she stomps easily.Sasuke looked so much like Madara that Sakura had to give him a haircut.Also here\u2019s when the novel was released :  and here\u2019s when it was adapted into the anime:  So you tell me which source material is more reliable  6> Konoha Shinden : Steam Ninja Scrolls  The anime adapted pretty much everything that happened in the novel. Here\u2019s when the novel was released :  And here\u2019s when it was adapted into the anime :  So you tell me which source material is more reliable.  The follwing are the novels which although have been canonized, were never adapted into the anime: Kakashi Hiden : Lightning in the Ice Sky Sakura Hiden : Thoughts of Love riding Upon a Spring Breeze Gaara Hiden : A Sandstorm Mirage Akatsuki Hiden : Evil Flowers in Full Bloom  Here are the novels which are yet to recieve an anime adaptation: Sasuke Shinden : The Teacher\u2019s Star Pupil Shikamaru Shinden : A Cloud Dancing in Forlorn Falling Petals Kakashi Retsuden : The Sixth Hokage and the Failure Boy Sasuke Retsuden : The Uchiha descendents and the Heavenly Stardust Naruto Retsuden : Naruto Uzumaki and the Spiral Destiny  The only novels which were canonized/ adapted from the anime are the : Naruto : The Last movie Novel Boruto : Naruto the Movie Novel The only difference between the movies and the novels is that in the \u201cLast Movie\u201d Novelisation, Rock Lee destroyed 2 meteors, the origins of the Otsutsukis have been described beautifully well and Naruto was hella horny and wanted to smash Hinata, whereas the Boruto Movie Novel did justice to Momoshiki and actually gave him feats that puts him on a pedastool over Kaguya! Mind you, the novelisation of the movies were done by Kishimoto himself!  The side characters who\u2019ve been neglected by Kishi have far better development and feats in the novels (except Tenten) and that\u2019s all the more reason to view them as canon source materials.  The Naruto Novels are canon and that\u2019s a bloody fact. Facts don\u2019t care about your feelings. Peace Out. ",
