            "answer_text": "No, I don\u2019t think so.   The novels are too inconsistent to be proved canon. B-but it was approved by Kishimoto Yes, it was. But from what I remember, wasn\u2019t the databooks too? And according to the databooks, Hebi Sasuke can beat all of Akatsuki. So should we accept it as facts like the novels? I don\u2019t really think it is on the same tier as the manga. There are so many inconsistencies in the Novels, for example- Naruto in the novels was able to dodge a lightspeed attack. But in Boruto, Momoshiki hit him a couple of time. And no, Momo is not the speed of light- he was blocked by Gaara\u2019s sand.   And then, there\u2019s also the fact that Momoshiki blew up a star. I feel really annoyed when people use this thing to make Base Momoshiki star level, like we don\u2019t even know how much prep time Momoshiki got.  All and all, I don\u2019t like using Novels to bring up feats. You know, it\u2019s kind of like the databooks, it at times you could use- however not EVERY thing here has to be logical. Just like Naruto got hit by a sword in the Boruto manga, which is completely illogical. The same way- Naruto dodging a light speed attack in BASE form, is also illogical. I think we should take the novels with a grain of salt, if it is contradicted in the anime/manga- it should be deemed untrue. ",
