            "answer_text": "Terry write a really good answer but he\u2019s half right. 1. Itachi novel: Itachi\u2019s story was disclosed in 2008. Throughout the series over and over Itachi\u2019s story has been shown. And last it was 3rd Hokage talk about Itachi when Sasuke asked about Itachi\u2019s truth and it was 2013. So about Itachi, everything was shown in Manga but in different panels. In the novel they gather all the information about Itachi which was in Manga and then published in 2015. And when SP animated they remove irrelevant parts which doesn\u2019t go with the story. Like Itachi killed Shisui, and his girlfriend. A 13 year boy, who was Anbu captain, was so much busy that he didn\u2019t have enough time for his dearest parson Sasuke, but does have time for having a girlfriend. Didn\u2019t think about any children or his parents but about his girlfriend\u2019s dream. Fugaku was uchiha leader and don\u2019t have MS \ud83e\udd37. Do you really want me to believe that? If you think that Itachi\u2019s story was taken from the novel. Then sorry you are wrong that was already on the manga. 2. Sasuke shinden: According to novel it took place 5 month after Naruto and Hinata\u2019s marriage. In war Naruto was 17, In Boruto Naruto said that it\u2019s been 15 years since war and Boruto is 12 years old.  So in between 15 years, The last took place 2 years after war, NaruHina got married after some time and immediately gets pregnant. It took 9 months to born a child. So I am considering that their dating, marriage and give birth in total 1 year (12 Month). If Sasuke shined took place 5 month after NaruHina wedding then how Sarada is just 4 days younger then Boruto. Does it make any sense? And about some part like Sakura told Naruto about Sasuke\u2019s dream of becoming Police officer. Seriously!!! Here is she telling Sasuke never tell anything to her before Sasuke leave the village.  After war Sasuke was in jail and then went for his redemption journey. Then when did he tell her? If Sasuke tell her, what did he tell \u201cI want to kill my brother then I\u2019ll be a police officer\u201d \ud83e\udd37 Doesn\u2019t make any sense. Naruto\u2019s last v-72 was released in February 4 2015 and Sasuke shinden release on November 4 2015. So they pick the plot form Naruto\u2019s last chapter about Sasuke\u2019s redemption journey. However again SP correct those mistakes and remove those irrelevant parts which doesn\u2019t go with the story . 3. About Shikamaru hidden . The last release on December 6 2014 and the novel release in March 4 2015, Naruto V-72 release February 4 2015. So the last release before end of the Manga and shikamaru hiden. And get animated as it fits in the timeline. 4. About the last (Dec- 6 2014) and Boruto movie (Aug 7 2015), that aren\u2019t a part of the light novels. First they release the movie then they published the script. Those aren\u2019t adopted from any novel. 5. About Konoha Hiden: Perfect day of wedding. this novel was needed for Boruto, Actually Sasuke shinden, shikamaru hidden, konoha hidden were for complete the Naruto story, as Kishi already started his work for Samirai 8. And About Boruto novels Boruto is full of fillers or Anime canon whatever it calls. 6. Naruto Shinden: Parents and Childs day. Again SP remove irrelevant parts, Such as if Boruto never left his home then why don\u2019t he go with Naruto as it was a parents Childs day. Sakura give Sasuke a haircut, Boruto took place in modern era, and how come there is no salon. Sorry I don\u2019t believe that Hanabi has this level of audacity to talk about Naruto. I mean how dare she (if they Animated those parts she would definitely replace Sakura as most hated Character) So again SP remove those irrelevant parts which doesn\u2019t go with the story. And won\u2019t affect the original story. 7. Konoha Shinden: Steam Ninja Scrolls. Doesn\u2019t have anything to do with Original story, but that was needed because of Mirai. 8. Now the novels which were never animated. That novel has nothing to do with the original story. If those novels fits in the original timeline doesn\u2019t make them canon. Do you know what else fits in the original time line? Fillers. 9. And now the novel which Are yet to receive an anime adaption. If they make any sense to the Story they will be animated, if they doesn\u2019t make any sense then they will never be animated. If they get an anime adaption the irrelevant parts will definitely be removed. Then how come all those novels are canon? 90% people don\u2019t read novels, only watch anime. 10% read, among them 5% don\u2019t give a f**k 3.5% believe those are not canon 1.5% believes those are canon At this level it really doesn\u2019t matter those light novels are canon or not. ",
